Interface ITask<T>

  • Type Parameters:

      • setOnCompleteListener

        ITask<T> setOnCompleteListener(OnCompleteListener<T> listener)
        Set a listener to receive a callback when the operation completes.

        Callbacks for OnCompleteListener will be made on the calling thread, which must already be a prepared looper thread, such as the main thread of the calling Activity. The variant of this method with a Looper is recommended for cases where the callback needs to happen on a specific thread. See setOnCompleteListener(OnCompleteListener, Looper).

        Parameters:
        listener - the listener for the result.
        Returns:
        this ITask for chaining calls
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the calling thread is not associated with a looper.

      • setOnCompleteListener

        ITask<T> setOnCompleteListener(OnCompleteListener<T> listener,
                               android.os.Looper looper)
        Set a listener to receive a callback when the operation completes.

        Callbacks for OnCompleteListener will be made on the specified thread, which must already be a prepared looper thread. For cases where the callback can happen on the calling thread, the variant of this method without a Looper can be used. See setOnCompleteListener(OnCompleteListener).

        Parameters:
        listener - the listener for the result.
        looper - the Looper object whose message queue will be used to implement the callback mechanism.
        Returns:
        this ITask for chaining calls
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if unable to retrieve looper.
